1
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,120
Dad!

2
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,640
Dad!

3
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:46,520
Dad!

4
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:07,640
Give my daughter back.

5
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:10,199
Or…

6
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:12,360
I won't leave,

7
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:14,480
even if you run me over a thousand times.

8
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:17,080
Don't chicken out.

9
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:18,560
Floor it!

10
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:20,200
Run him over!

11
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,280
Dad!

12
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:23,080
Don't hit my dad!

13
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,080
Dad!

14
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,280
Dad!

15
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,960
Give my daughter…

16
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:38,280
back.

17
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,320
Turn around. Run.

18
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:54,360
That's what you get
for running over my dad!

19
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:55,280
How can you run over my dad!

20
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,680
Sir!

21
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:59,480
That's what you get
for running over my dad!

22
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:01,280
That's what you get
for running over my dad!

23
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:03,000
- Xiaohe.
- How dare you!

24
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:04,960
- Xiaohe.
- How dare you!

25
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:07,280
- Quick.
- Dad!

26
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:08,280
Dad!

27
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:11,240
Dad! Wake up!

28
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:13,320
Don't sleep. Dad!

29
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,920
Wake up.

30
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:18,520
Wake up, Dad! Dad!

31
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:24,360
Xiaohe.

32
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:26,600
I'm fine.

33
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:30,560
Am I rocking it

34
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,920
today?

35
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,600
- Wake up, Dad!
- Sir!

36
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,840
Don't sleep!

37
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:44,960
Sir.

38
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,640
- Quick. Call an ambulance.
- Okay.

39
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:49,200
Sir!

40
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:51,120
Hurry. Drag him out. Quick.

41
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:53,640
Sir!

42
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:55,960
- Wake up! Don't sleep, sir!
- How is he?

43
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:57,920
His bones are fine.

44
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,320
Sir. Sir. Don't sleep.

45
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,240
Mei said there was a roadblock
on the highway.

46
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:04,360
Turn left at the next intersection.
There's a workshop.

47
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,400
<i>He'll be waiting for us there.</i>

48
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:06,440
Uncle Ran.

49
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:08,440
The human traffickers are there.

50
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,720
HOMELY WORKSHOP

51
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:28,320
AHAO AUTO MAINTENANCE

52
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:29,480
POLICE

53
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,320
Qu.

54
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:40,040
This is the only construction area

55
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:41,280
within all three schools.

56
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:44,440
Only this spot
doesn't have security cameras.

57
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:52,760
Let's get to work.

58
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,520
Mister, I need your help.

59
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,080
Have you seen these kids?

60
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:06,680
Do you know anyone here who gives rides?

61
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:07,640
No.

62
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,280
Have you seen these kids?

63
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,480
Have you seen these kids?

64
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:12,840
- Have you seen these five kids?
- No.

65
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,440
I don't know them.

66
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,800
I don't have a car.

67
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:25,480
I always use a trolley to restock.

68
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:27,880
All right then.

69
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:31,280
Wait.

70
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:34,360
Someone who gives rides?
You can ask that shop.

71
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:36,560
The owner loves to give people rides

72
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:39,000
when he restocks.

73
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:40,400
He is quite scary-looking.

74
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:44,120
I heard that he was imprisoned once
for kidnapping.

75
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:46,280
Gaoyishou?

76
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:54,720
The chef is on a break.

77
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,280
We open at five.

78
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,600
Where is your boss?

79
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:01,720
We're from the Nanshan Branch.
We're asking about people giving rides.

80
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,840
He went home to sleep.
Please return at 4:30 p.m.

81
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,000
Stand right there!

82
00:07:26,840 --> 00:07:28,760
It hurts! Madam. Not so rough.

83
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:30,360
It hurts!

84
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:31,560
Not so rough.

85
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:33,400
Not so rough. It hurts.

86
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:34,920
PROSPEROUS BUSINESS

87
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:38,320
I've never given kids a ride.

88
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:41,400
You can check the dashcam in my car.

89
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,200
What's with your criminal record
of kidnapping?

90
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:45,960
Who told you that?

91
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,520
Was it the woman from--

92
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:50,640
Just answer my question.

93
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,560
I already served my sentence.

94
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,120
What more do you want?

95
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:57,840
Fine.

96
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,360
It was an argument with my wife.

97
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,040
My wife…

98
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,720
Well, my ex-wife

99
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,280
returned to her parents' place
to hide from me.

100
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:07,800
I was mad,

101
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:09,880
so I kidnapped her and starved her.

102
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:11,720
I was jailed for three years.

103
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:13,800
Mr. Officer.

104
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:16,720
I give people rides
when I'm out restocking.

105
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,320
Is that a crime?

106
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:20,680
Do you have to pin me down and arrest me?

107
00:08:20,760 --> 00:08:22,440
Why did you run just now?

108
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:25,800
I was arrested once.

109
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,480
Whenever I see police officers,

110
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:31,040
my legs begin moving before I know it.

111
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,600
Dad.

112
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,000
What?

113
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:41,840
Isn't she the host on the TV channel?

114
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,680
That's him.

115
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:48,520
I can recognize him,
even if he has turned into ashes.

116
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:56,960
Mei.

117
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:59,360
He's still in Weiyang.

118
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:13,600
Why aren't they picking up?

119
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:21,800
<i>Hello, Officer He?</i>

120
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:22,880
Hey, Ms. Wang.

121
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,640
Can you check if there are
needlestick injuries on Han Zi'ang?

122
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:41,400
<i>Officer He. I found some.</i>

123
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:44,800
<i>I found two on his right arm.</i>

124
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:52,960
Mei is a regular
among the wanted criminals.

125
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:55,200
He is involved
in many child trafficking cases.

126
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:57,760
He is cunning and good
at disguising himself.

127
00:09:57,840 --> 00:10:00,440
He has not been arrested
for more than a decade.

128
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:02,320
Based on the information given
by Officer He Xiaohe,

129
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,480
we can deduce

130
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:05,480
that Mei lurks around

131
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,640
the construction area near Fuxing Street.

132
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:11,120
<i>He stalks students who skip classes</i>
<i>to hang out at the illegal internet cafe.</i>

133
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:14,800
<i>Then, he injects them with anesthetics</i>
<i>before kidnapping them.</i>

134
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:26,880
The last victim, Han Zi'ang,

135
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:29,040
is quite different
from the four previous victims.

136
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:32,440
<i>We believe that after Han Zi'ang</i>
<i>left the internet cafe,</i>

137
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:34,040
<i>he didn't go home.</i>

138
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:36,440
<i>Instead, he went to the 18th floor</i>

139
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:39,120
<i>of New York Block</i>
<i>to explore out of curiosity.</i>

140
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:05,240
Help! Help! Help!

141
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:08,600
Help! Help!

142
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:12,600
After Han Zi'ang,

143
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:13,960
there has been no new victim.

144
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,000
PERSON OF INTEREST: MEI

145
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:18,200
That means Han Zi'ang's escape
disrupted Mei's plan.

146
00:11:18,280 --> 00:11:20,680
He had no choice but to stop.
His priority now

147
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:23,280
is to bring those four victims
out of Weiyang.

148
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:25,640
Bai, Hui. Print out the wanted posters.

149
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:27,600
Make sure the photo is huge.

150
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:29,480
Then, let others post them everywhere.

151
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:31,840
Xing. Investigate
all egresses of the city.

152
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:33,040
Check the cameras of bus stations
and train stations

153
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:34,000
to see if the culprit

154
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,680
- has left Weiyang with the victims.
- Got it.

155
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:38,560
Mangkun. Bring some men with you
and investigate the motels, hostels,

156
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,400
or warehouses of the district.

157
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:42,600
The culprit might be hiding
the victims there

158
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:43,640
before buyers appear.

159
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:45,040
Guys. Split up.

160
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:53,600
Xiaohe,

161
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:55,320
you provided a useful lead.

162
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:57,920
I allow you to work
with the Special Task Force.

163
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,280
Thank you, sir.

164
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,520
But given the urgency,
is casting your net wide

165
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:02,960
the best way to do it?

166
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:05,800
If not, we wait for Mei
to turn himself in?

167
00:12:05,880 --> 00:12:07,000
- But… But we are running out--
- Sorry. Captain Qu.

168
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:09,400
Xiaohe. Let's go.

169
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:10,640
Why?

170
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:22,960
Your deposition was excellent.

171
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:25,320
And your dad is almost recovered.

172
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:37,360
Xiaohe,

173
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:40,080
I owe you an apology.

174
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:42,480
It was my fault.

175
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:43,680
I was too harsh on you.

176
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:46,480
If I had put myself in your shoes,

177
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,320
things wouldn't have ended this way.

178
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:51,280
You wouldn't have run into danger.

179
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,320
I ask for your forgiveness.

180
00:12:57,760 --> 00:12:58,760
No need to apologize.

181
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:03,000
I made this mess.

182
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,160
And I will own up.

183
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,200
You have no idea

184
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:18,320
how worried your dad was
when he heard that you were in danger.

185
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:21,440
He hailed a cab overnight at Mount Wu
and traveled over 400 kilometers here.

186
00:13:21,520 --> 00:13:22,360
I know.

187
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:28,600
When he stood before the van,

188
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,720
I already knew it.

189
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:32,920
Xiaohe.

190
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,080
It's okay, Uncle Ran.

191
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:37,840
Don't worry about me.

192
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:40,040
And no need to console me.

193
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,640
I'm strong.

194
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:47,200
Anyway, what happened
to Melon and the rest?

195
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,360
Who?

196
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:51,280
Those four guys on the esports team.

197
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:53,760
After you raided the internet cafe,

198
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:56,160
are they homeless now?

199
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:08,960
Aren't we heading home?

200
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:29,560
Eat slowly.

201
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:34,000
Oh. Have you found a new base?

202
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:44,200
We have been thinking a lot lately.

203
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,680
There is no future in esports.

204
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:47,680
It's better to go back home.

205
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:50,080
We plan to work

206
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:52,160
in a factory after the Chinese New Year.

207
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:57,560
Who says there's no future in esports?

208
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:03,000
It's the 21st century.

209
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,880
As long as you work with computers,

210
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:06,280
you have a future.

211
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:10,440
Besides, all of you have worked
and trained so hard.

212
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:12,200
If you don't have a match
with someone else,

213
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:13,720
you'll bring shame to your own hard work.

214
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:14,920
Exactly.

215
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,400
What about the eggs I bought you guys?

216
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:22,400
I know several cheap
and legit internet cafes.

217
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:24,960
All of you will go to the police station
to get your identity cards done

218
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:26,120
to prove that you're adults.

219
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,800
Then, you can practice there.

220
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:35,200
Here.

221
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:47,680
Consider this an investment from me.

222
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:49,320
Once you become popular,

223
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:51,040
visit the Criminal Department
and pay me back.

224
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:55,960
Thank you, Officer Ran.

225
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:57,880
Dig in.

226
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:11,160
Come. An extra braised egg for you.

227
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:14,000
You're awesome, Uncle Ran.

228
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,680
You're my idol for life.

229
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:17,120
I'm so proud of you.

230
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:18,680
Another chicken drumstick for you.

231
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:50,200
What?

232
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:53,080
Is my cholesterol not high enough?

233
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:55,520
Forget it then.

234
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:58,440
You can't put food
in my bowl and take it away.

235
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:09,560
Uncle Ran,

236
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:12,880
Melon and the guys
are ambitious, aren't they?

237
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:15,880
They are good kids.

238
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:17,800
They work hard and are committed.

239
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:20,599
Why else did I give them
two months of my salary?

240
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:21,640
Then,

241
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:25,720
perhaps you should
support my dream as well.

242
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,880
I want to study music in Beijing.

243
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,920
I work hard and am committed.

244
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,800
Music is not a proper job.

245
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:34,120
Your priority now is to study

246
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:36,240
and get into a good university.

247
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:40,080
You were brave and smart inside the van

248
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,560
with the human traffickers.

249
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:43,400
You can be a criminal police officer.

250
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:47,480
Do you want to join the police force
and make use of your talent?

251
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,680
Actually,

252
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:53,760
being an officer like you sounds cool.

253
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:56,760
You

254
00:17:57,280 --> 00:18:00,280
will never be an excellent cop like Ran.

255
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:01,880
Excuse me?

256
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,440
I am just as smart as him,

257
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:04,600
and I'm stronger than him.

258
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:10,920
You can have your opinion.
I won't stop you.

259
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,120
Just promise me

260
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:13,520
that you'll study hard.

261
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,240
After you graduate from high school,

262
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:16,560
I'll send you to Beijing to study music.

263
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:18,480
Why not after middle school?

264
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:19,880
You have to graduate first.

265
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,840
Be a literate rock artist.

266
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:22,760
He's right.

267
00:18:22,840 --> 00:18:25,160
Don't just rock and roll.

268
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:28,840
- Deal.
- Deal.

269
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:31,200
We don't do that anymore.

270
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:40,080
Deal.

271
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:41,800
I will study now then.

272
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:48,440
She is skipping her meal.

273
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:57,600
Sir.

274
00:18:59,360 --> 00:19:00,640
Xiaohe wrote this song.

275
00:19:01,320 --> 00:19:03,920
Listen to it when you're free.
I think she's good.

276
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:05,520
- Really?
- Yes.

277
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:11,440
RESTRICTED AREA

278
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:17,720
Let's have a drink.

279
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:20,680
Sir.

280
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:23,560
Your body hasn't recovered.
The doctor said you shouldn't drink.

281
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:26,720
For this occasion, we must.

282
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:40,800
Without you,

283
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:44,560
my family would be all gone.

284
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:49,400
I would be all alone for real.

285
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:51,200
Thank you.

286
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:56,520
Back then in the hospital,
you told me not to be sappy.

287
00:19:57,040 --> 00:19:58,640
Look who's being sappy now.

288
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:01,440
Right.

289
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,040
Oh, sir.

290
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:11,800
Did you find anything useful on your trip?

291
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:17,400
I told you not to drink,
but you wouldn't listen.

292
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,480
Have some water.

293
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,680
Sir,

294
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:29,560
I'll request the higher-ups
to give you a longer break.

295
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,880
HE YUANHANG, SECOND-CLASS MERIT

296
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,480
I can't take my wage
without working for it.

297
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:44,560
I want to give it one last shot

298
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:47,040
and investigate Yuanlongli again.

299
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:50,800
Even if I find nothing in the end,

300
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:55,360
at the very least, I can close
the chapter once and for all.

301
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:12,000
MISSING PERSON TURNED INTO KIDNAP

302
00:21:12,080 --> 00:21:13,560
FOUR TEENAGERS STILL MISSING

303
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:16,600
ARE THE POLICE USELESS?

304
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:17,960
ARE THEY DEAD OR ALIVE?

305
00:21:24,840 --> 00:21:26,480
How many days till the deadline?

306
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,720
Captain Qu. Permission
to assign several policemen

307
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:39,240
to assist me.

308
00:21:39,320 --> 00:21:41,320
I want to give it my last shot.

309
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,400
Captain Qu.

310
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:45,040
I'd like to work with Xiaohe.

311
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:48,120
I want to work with Xiaohe too.

312
00:21:51,760 --> 00:21:53,920
He is the support I found for us.

313
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,360
Old He, help us show them
what we're capable of.

314
00:21:58,320 --> 00:22:00,240
Old He?

315
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:02,240
Who are you calling old here?

316
00:22:02,320 --> 00:22:03,560
Sorry.

317
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:06,840
Perhaps we should just call you Mr. He.

318
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:08,320
- Say it.
- Mr. He.

319
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:10,000
That's nice.

320
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:11,320
Mr. He,

321
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,720
how will we investigate Yuanlongli?

322
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:15,920
Mei is involved in many abduction cases.

323
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:18,280
He is cunning and good at disguising.

324
00:22:18,360 --> 00:22:21,880
We cannot predict what he will do
by using a logical mind.

325
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:23,760
For a serial abductor,

326
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:27,760
the most dangerous place
is the safest place.

327
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:30,320
That's how they hide under our noses.

328
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:32,720
Dad. Just cut to the chase.

329
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:35,920
Yuanlongli will be redeveloped soon.

330
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,840
Many residents have moved away.

331
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:39,960
All those empty units

332
00:22:40,040 --> 00:22:43,880
are the perfect hiding spot for Mei.

333
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:46,800
Dad, how come you are so sure

334
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:48,520
that Mei will be hiding under our noses?

335
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:49,480
I'm not sure.

336
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:54,360
But I have a feeling
that there's something more

337
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:57,000
hiding in Yuanlongli.

338
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:23,520
Officer He, you came to work again.

339
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:28,720
Ma Qiang. Fire safety
is very important during winter.

340
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:29,960
- All of you…
- Officer He.

341
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:31,240
Officer He, you're here again.

342
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:35,600
Honestly though, he has worked
as a policeman for so long.

343
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:37,880
He finally cracked a big case

344
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:39,120
and got a Second-Class Merit.

345
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:40,800
Also, it was Officer Ran
who let him claim the credit.

346
00:23:41,480 --> 00:23:44,000
I also heard that his health is bad.

347
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:45,600
He is claiming disability aid now.

348
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:49,200
Wasn't the case closed already?

349
00:23:49,280 --> 00:23:51,040
Why is he still in Yuanlongli?

350
00:23:52,280 --> 00:23:53,680
He can't move on.

351
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:55,880
He needs to feel useful.

352
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:12,680
Go. Carry it. Quick.

353
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:15,560
You two. It's good enough.

354
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:16,960
Good enough. Hurry up now.

355
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,200
Hurry up.

356
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,000
Oh my!

357
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:23,240
Officer He.

358
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:25,360
What are you doing here?

359
00:25:29,040 --> 00:25:31,080
I'm here to look for leads.

360
00:25:31,160 --> 00:25:34,040
Give me the keys to the management office
of New York Block.

361
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:38,640
The keys…

362
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:43,040
Follow me to the office.

363
00:25:44,120 --> 00:25:45,440
Come.

364
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:53,760
Officer He.

365
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:56,080
The keys?

366
00:25:56,920 --> 00:25:57,920
What did you do?

367
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:03,480
I… We are building a cement block.

368
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:09,520
Seriously?

369
00:26:10,120 --> 00:26:11,400
A cement block here?

370
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:13,360
Many people walk here. It's inconvenient.

371
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:15,120
I'm trying to be considerate.

372
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:17,960
The workers push
their wheelbarrows around.

373
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:19,840
A barricade here

374
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:22,840
can remind them not to hit anyone.

375
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:32,040
The keys.

376
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:36,080
Let's go.

377
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:41,680
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY
BUREAU NANSHAN BRANCH

378
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:48,280
POLICE BY THE PEOPLE
FOR THE PEOPLE

379
00:26:48,360 --> 00:26:49,280
I was looking for you, Fangxu.

380
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:51,200
Mei's accomplices confessed everything.

381
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:52,640
But they do not know where his base is.

382
00:26:52,720 --> 00:26:53,960
Their communication
has always been unilateral.

383
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:58,280
Grab a screenshot
from the internet cafe's footage.

384
00:26:58,360 --> 00:26:59,720
Then, update Mei's photo

385
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:00,720
- in our internal system.
- Okay.

386
00:27:02,600 --> 00:27:04,360
Madam. Madam. Madam.

387
00:27:04,960 --> 00:27:06,000
I'm looking for the criminal police.

388
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:06,920
What's the matter?

389
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:07,960
I want to report a case.

390
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:10,000
Come. Let's get you registered first.

391
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:11,840
It's urgent. I need to report a case.

392
00:27:11,920 --> 00:27:13,040
Wu.

393
00:27:13,760 --> 00:27:15,280
- Captain Ran.
- Madam.

394
00:27:15,360 --> 00:27:16,680
Why are you looking
for the criminal police?

395
00:27:16,760 --> 00:27:18,080
I want to report a case.

396
00:27:18,160 --> 00:27:19,160
A murder in Yuanlongli.

397
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:33,960
This place is foul.

398
00:27:34,040 --> 00:27:36,120
I rented this place for three years,

399
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:38,440
and I had to pay for so many things.

400
00:27:38,520 --> 00:27:39,520
Buddy,

401
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:40,680
are you looking for a place to stay?

402
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:42,200
Run away now.

403
00:27:42,280 --> 00:27:43,840
This place only has bad luck.

404
00:27:43,920 --> 00:27:45,000
It's haunted.

405
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:46,600
Just run. Save yourself.

406
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:48,360
Whoever stays here is cursed.

407
00:27:58,640 --> 00:28:01,240
HUAINAN TEMPLE

408
00:28:17,720 --> 00:28:19,280
Mister,

409
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:21,320
you seem troubled.

410
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:23,480
Allow me to draw you

411
00:28:23,560 --> 00:28:25,400
an evil-cleansing talisman.

412
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:26,640
Come.

413
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:28,840
Come.

414
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:33,240
Don't be so rough. Please.

415
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:35,120
- Don't be so rough.
- Spread superstitions again

416
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:37,160
- and I will arrest you.
- Don't be so rough.

417
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:39,240
Don't be so rough.

418
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:40,480
RAN

419
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:41,800
- Don't be so rough.
- Shut up.

420
00:28:43,640 --> 00:28:45,280
- Sir.
- It hurts.

421
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:46,200
<i>Where are you?</i>

422
00:28:46,280 --> 00:28:47,640
Where else can I be?

423
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:49,080
<i>Come back to the station.</i>

424
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:51,000
Let me investigate the floor first.

425
00:28:51,080 --> 00:28:52,520
<i>No need.</i>

426
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:55,320
<i>We may no longer need to visit Yuanlongli.</i>

427
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:02,120
<i>I'm not scared.</i>

428
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:03,800
<i>I have money.</i>

429
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:05,640
<i>I can kill many people,</i>
<i>and others will take the blame for me.</i>

430
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:06,560
<i>You can't do anything.</i>

431
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:08,640
<i>You can't do anything to me!</i>

432
00:29:09,360 --> 00:29:11,720
<i>You have two options.</i>

433
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:13,600
<i>One, I'll burn the photos,</i>

434
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:15,440
<i>and you'll go somewhere to lay low.</i>

435
00:29:15,520 --> 00:29:16,400
<i>Two,</i>

436
00:29:16,480 --> 00:29:19,120
<i>I'll send the photos and the recording</i>
<i>to the police.</i>

437
00:29:19,640 --> 00:29:22,160
<i>Do you want your freedom and money?</i>

438
00:29:22,240 --> 00:29:23,320
<i>It's your choice.</i>

439
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:30,560
Director Li of Dongshan Mine
killed himself inside the police station

440
00:29:30,640 --> 00:29:31,680
five years ago.

441
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:33,560
Today, his surviving wife
came to report a case.

442
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:36,760
She claimed to have found
Director Li's hidden photos

443
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:38,800
and recordings when she was moving out.

444
00:29:39,400 --> 00:29:43,440
This suggests Director Li
coerced Song Qingsong into leaving.

445
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:46,320
But how did Director Li get these photos?

446
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:49,880
Only two people had the opportunity
to give Director Li the photos.

447
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:52,360
Cripple Du. Wu Shanlong.

448
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:54,360
I'm inclined to believe
it was Wu Shanlong.

449
00:29:54,440 --> 00:29:55,720
After all, he stood to profit the most

450
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:57,760
after Song Qingsong left.

451
00:29:57,840 --> 00:30:00,040
We also found a photocopy
of the tender document

452
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:02,560
inside Wu Shanlong's home.

453
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:04,680
While he refused to admit
that he kept the document,

454
00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:07,120
it doesn't mean
that he didn't use the photocopy

455
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:09,000
to blackmail Song Qingsong.

456
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:10,880
I even suspect

457
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:13,760
that the blackmailing letter
written to Song Qingsong by Xu Meng

458
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:14,960
was forged by him.

459
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:20,120
Song Qingsong never would have thought

460
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:22,880
that his brother-in-law was the one
who sabotaged him.

461
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:30,760
Unfortunately, she failed to escape.

462
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:42,560
The main culprit, Wu Shanlong, is dead.

463
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:44,880
The one who hired a hitman, Song Qingsong,

464
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:46,920
fled abroad for many years.

465
00:30:48,520 --> 00:30:51,760
All we can do now
is to release a wanted poster.

466
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:55,440
But I don't understand one thing.

467
00:30:56,760 --> 00:30:59,520
Wu Shanlong isn't smart.

468
00:31:01,200 --> 00:31:03,560
How could he devise so many plans?

469
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:21,000
Ms. Zhao, you're out.

470
00:31:21,080 --> 00:31:23,120
Ms. Zhao, you look so beautiful.

471
00:31:23,200 --> 00:31:25,400
After our new treatment,

472
00:31:25,480 --> 00:31:26,880
you look younger and prettier.

473
00:31:28,120 --> 00:31:30,560
I have solid genes. My heels.

474
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:32,840
XINXIN BEAUTY SALON

475
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:35,120
Young girls like you

476
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:37,320
shouldn't just chase
after physical beauty blindly.

477
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:40,120
A woman's real charisma
doesn't come from her face,

478
00:31:40,760 --> 00:31:41,880
but here.

479
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:48,000
Ms. Zhao. The balance
on your membership card is running low.

480
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:49,640
Do you want to…

481
00:31:52,320 --> 00:31:53,120
Top up another 10,000 yuan.

482
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:56,800
How generous of you, Ms. Zhao.

483
00:31:57,320 --> 00:31:58,720
Men are unreliable.

484
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:01,080
As women, we should treat ourselves.

485
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:02,000
See you.

486
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:04,400
Bye, Ms. Zhao.

487
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:05,600
Come back again.

488
00:32:05,680 --> 00:32:07,040
Drive safely.

489
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:09,920
I'm so sick of her.

490
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:11,080
Listen.

491
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:13,640
She used to open
a foot massage parlor too.

492
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:15,760
She found a guy called Wu Shanlong,

493
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:18,160
and they both took over a cement factory.

494
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:20,200
That's how she became rich.

495
00:32:20,280 --> 00:32:22,240
- Is that so?
- Yes.

496
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:25,000
So, she still relied on a man in the end.

497
00:33:06,040 --> 00:33:09,080
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

498
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:22,160
Ma Qiang. Give me the list of Yuanlongli's
current residents and tenants.

499
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:23,280
Several copies of it.

500
00:33:23,360 --> 00:33:25,840
Officer He, what is this for?

501
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:27,240
Just do what you're told.

502
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:34,640
How many units have been vacated?

503
00:33:34,720 --> 00:33:35,920
Many.

504
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:37,680
They are marked in red there.

505
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:40,320
2015 YUANLONGLI PROPERTY
OWNER/TENANT ROSTER

506
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:41,680
It seems like we have a busy night ahead.

507
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:43,160
Let's split up.

508
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:46,000
Zheng Zhong, you, Bai, and Hui
are in charge of Floors 1 to 9.

509
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:47,480
Xiaohe and I will check the ones upstairs.

510
00:33:47,560 --> 00:33:49,400
Use the walkie-talkie
if you find anything.

511
00:33:49,480 --> 00:33:50,480
Understood.

512
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:06,440
DEMOLITION

513
00:34:20,120 --> 00:34:21,920
The vacant units on the eastern side
of the 4th floor

514
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:23,040
are 13 and 16.

515
00:34:23,719 --> 00:34:24,560
Let's check 13 first.

516
00:35:56,640 --> 00:35:58,440
It hurts! Be gentle. It hurts!

517
00:35:58,520 --> 00:35:59,840
Shut up!

518
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:14,440
An escape room?

519
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:17,880
Do you even have the license for it?

520
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:20,240
It's so late at night.

521
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:22,600
You're doing this instead of sleeping.

522
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:25,000
This is a nuisance, do you hear me?

523
00:36:25,840 --> 00:36:27,120
Sorry, sir.

524
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:28,280
We've made a mistake.

525
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:29,480
We've made a mistake.

526
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:30,440
We'll leave now.

527
00:36:30,520 --> 00:36:31,760
- Now.
- Go.

528
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:32,880
Sorry, sir.

529
00:36:32,960 --> 00:36:34,440
Sorry. Sorry.

530
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:39,960
<i>Mr. He. Mr. He.</i>

531
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:42,920
<i>We've searched all nine floors.</i>
<i>Nothing unusual.</i>

532
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:46,120
Copy.

533
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:53,080
RESIDENTS
TENANTS REGISTRATION FORM

534
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:56,880
RESIDENT, TENANT, RESIDENT

535
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:01,600
Dad, Mei loves to use a fake identity.

536
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:03,600
He can rent a place using a fake identity.

537
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:05,840
How many tenants are here?

538
00:37:20,960 --> 00:37:22,280
HE YIQIANG

539
00:37:23,840 --> 00:37:24,800
HAO YOUQIANG

540
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:29,240
QIANG WEI'AN, WU QIANGYI, WANG ZIQIANG

